# Python coding style

- Prefer the fewest lines that stay clear; avoid ceremony and boilerplate.
- Keep design flat and direct. No factories, strategy objects, deep inheritance, or other patterns unless they remove real duplication.
- Use plain functions and simple data structures over abstractions.
- Comments are rare: one short line only when intent is not obvious from the code.
- Do not add block docstrings or multi-line comment blocks for obvious code.

## Prefer

```python
def send_reply(channel, text):
    return channel.send(text[:2000])
```

## Avoid

```python
class MessageSender(ABC):
  @abstractmethod
  def send(self, channel: Channel, payload: MessagePayload) -> None: ...
```